                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d840">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12612.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to Mexico to
                        the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 26, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>98. As stated in my No. 96, July 24, the President appointed today as his
                    delegates to the conference with the Constitutionalists the following: General
                    Lauro Villar, Chief Justice of the Supreme Military Court, and Licenciado David
                    Gutiérrez Allende, Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of Mexico, who will
                    leave tomorrow morning accompanied by one secretary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
